                <h3 class="primaryPurpleFont mobileHeaderStack">Our Story</h3>
                <p>
                  While today's social networks have been tremendously successful in "connecting" people across the globe, it is less clear
                  that it is making us better people. Afterall, how much quality interaction would you say you've engaged in online? Does
                  pressing an emoji button actually connect you with your friend online? Maybe, but more likely it was done in passing
                  without much thought.
                  <br /><br />
                  There is also growing evidence that high levels of social media use can lead to physical
                  and mental health problems ranging from lower back pain to depression. We spend to many hour craning our necks awkwardly
                  towards our phones comparing our lives to the best version your "friends" can filter through rose-colored glass-filters apps.
                  Shouldn't what we do with our screen time make us feel BETTER, not worse?
                  <br /><br />
                  At Aurealius we wanted to build something different. Inpsired by the likes of great stoics like Marcus Aurelius (from whom
                  we derive our name), we set out to build a platform rooted in the ancient philosophy of stoicism, where gratitude
                  and appreciation support the acknowledgement of the world as it is, not as we wish it to be. No more effortless judgement,
                  professional image filters, and arguing about politics. Aurealius is for those who want their screen time to REDUCE
                  stress through a selectively-social gratitude practice.
                  <br /><br />
                </p>
