                  <h4 class="primaryPurpleFont">Scott Kirker</h4>
                  <p>Since graduating from Penn State University in 2006, Scott's career has been predominantly focused on mergers and acquisitions and finance.
                    His experience includes investment banking, private equity and corporate finance.
                    <br /><br />
                    For years he dreamed of building something meaningful
                    on his own. Too often he yearned to be the entrepreneur on the other side of the table while in his professional roles. He could see their sense
                    of purpose and pride in their work. He admired their commitment to action, even if it came at the expense of conventional wisdom. He found inspiration
                    in their stories.
                    <br /><br />
                    So, Scott decided to pursue an MBA from Babson College, a program famous for its strength in entrepreneurship. After graduating in 2012, he kept his eyes
                    open for inspiration to strike. He founded Ultimately five years later with the encouragement and support of his loved ones and mentors.
                    <br /><br />
                    Scott is a certified life coach and full stack developer, skills that have been invaluable in his efforts to discover ways to help people fulfill their
                    life goals with the help of technology. He has consistently sought out ways to implement best practices from his experiences in to the platform.
                  </p>
